<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: You are far from Stupid, you hit EVIL on the mark!!</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?isildur">isildur</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 4:09 p.m. 23/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: You are far from Stupid, you hit EVIL on the mark!!<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1617" TARGET=_self>You are far from Stupid, you hit EVIL on the mark!!</A> (Holly Golightly (Petunia, Ogre Shaman))
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> There are a ton of 12 year old

<BR>&gt; dewds out there that think using the loot bug is evil. It's not
<BR>&gt; evil, it's just being a jerk.
<P><delurk>
<P>l33t d00dz aren't evil, and, by the same token, neither are the majority of the 'evil' races. in fact, they seem to be the least evil of the bunch. they're (by everything i've been reading) loyal within race lines, and within faction lines, help each other out, stick together. that ain't evil.
<P>which is something i love about EQ's vision of morality. no absolutes, just loyalties.
<P>Now if you want to play an *evil* dark elf, spend a month getting into someone's confidence. Then, the moment it seems profitable, kill them. Play a human and make arrangements to betray your city to the dark elves. Turn on your comrades in the midst of a huge fight. Steal from people who are helping you. Lead a party of lower-level people into certain death vs. monsters, refuse to help them -- root them if you can! -- and then, cackling, loot their corpses when it's all over. 'Forget' to heal someone at a critical moment. Never forget a slight (write it down if you have to), and get revenge weeks or months later. Done with proper RP, these actions would be reprehensible but justifiable, and would make you 'evil'. Notice that it would also make you all alone :>
<P>But summoning skeletons to defend your friends and fellow dark elves? That's what i would define as, uhm, good.
<P>-isildur
<BR>
